23/01/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The war crimes court in Belgrade has sentenced nine former Kosovo Albanian rebels for war crimes against Serbian civilians in the summer of 1999.
The nine, members of the Kosovo Liberation Army's Gnjilane Group, were sentenced on Friday (January 21st) to a total of 101 years in prison.
They were found guilty of killing of 80 Serb and non-Albanian civilians and illegally detaining more than 150 civilians in Gnjilane between June and September.
(Tanjug, RTS, Beta, B92 - 21/01/11)
